SUMMARY:Drawing and Understanding Conifer Trees in Micron Pen
DESCRIPTION:Register Here\n\nwith Stacy-Ann Searle\, Landscape Artist \nDate: Thursday\, March 12\, 2026\nTime: 9:30 a.m. – 3:30 p.m.\nLocation: North Carolina Botanical Garden\nFee: $78 ($70 Members) \n  \nConifers come in many varieties. In this three-session workshop\, we will explore how to capture the different overarching structure of these trees\, as well as a variety of leaf/needle forms and bark textures. For this class\, we will be using micron pens to create a variety of small ink studies. Students will gain an understanding of the different mark making techniques\, how to create textures in ink and gain confidence in using this very approachable ink medium. \n  \nRegister Here
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/drawing-and-understanding-conifer-trees-in-micron-pen/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Learn
GEO:35.901081;-79.031939
