SUMMARY:Spring Break Camp (Grades 1st-3rd)
DESCRIPTION:Register Here\n\nGrades: 1st – 3rd\nDate: Monday\, March 30 – April 2 (no camp on Friday)\nTime: 9:00 AM – 3:00 PM *Drop-off: 8:45-9 a.m.; Pick-up: 3-3:15 p.m.\nLocation: North Carolina Botanical Garden\nFee: $290 ($262 Household & above Members) \nSchool’s out for spring break? Send your nature lover to a week full of hands-on outdoor discovery celebrating the change of season.  \nJoin us for an adventure through the four elements—earth\, water\, air\, and fire—and discover how each one helps our native plants and animals thrive! Campers will dig into the soil to uncover life underground\, explore the magic of water and how it shapes habitats\, discover flying seeds\, and learn how fire helps forests grow anew. Each day includes hands-on science activities\, nature hikes\, creative crafts\, and storytelling that connects these powerful elements to the living world around us. \n  \nRegister Here
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/spring-break-camp-grades-1st-3rd/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Learn
GEO:35.901081;-79.031939
