SUMMARY:Chapel Hill Garden Tour
DESCRIPTION:Join the Chapel Hill Garden Club for the 2026 Chapel Hill Garden Tour! Our main garden is one of the stops – along with five distinctive private Chapel Hill-area gardens where unique visions of beauty\, preservation\, sustainability and design are on full display. \nGuided by knowledgeable experts\, see stunning spring blooms\, majestic trees and rock formations. Explore a butterfly sanctuary\, a tranquil Japanese garden\, and a plant lover’s paradise. \nDates \nSaturday\, April 25 and Sunday\, April 26 \n10 a.m. to 4 p.m. \nGuided Tours \nTicket-holders are invited to join us for guided tours of our main garden at 11 a.m. and 2 p.m. on both Saturday and Sunday. \nTickets \nTickets are $30 in advance and $40 day-of. Purchase tickets online now through Eventbrite or with cash or check in-person in our Garden Shop starting on April 1. \nProceeds support the North Carolina Botanical Garden and the Chapel Hill Garden Club’s many community service projects. Learn more about the Chapel Hill Garden Club.
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/chapel-hill-garden-tour/2026-04-25/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Special Events
GEO:35.901081;-79.031939
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=North Carolina Botanical Garden 100 Old Mason Farm Road Chapel Hill NC 27517 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=100 Old Mason Farm Road:geo:-79.031939,35.901081
END:VEVENT
